"A new cat is introduced and sings a song..." Well, okay. That's not the movie's fault.

"Cats", itself, is just a bunch of character introductions.

Problem is, that doesn't work as a movie. Kind of like "Hair" - on stage, it's... a bunch of character introductions and vignettes, but the movie managed to write a cinematic plot that still managed to feature those songs. "Cats" did not.
